"y": 308.390625, "top": 308.390625, "left": 0, "right": 1077, "width": 1077, "bottom": 3428.7421875, "height": 3120.3515625}, "type": "click", "model": "guide", "tabId": 1792158059, "title": "Click About the job\n\n\nAs Product Manager on the Disruption team, you will work at the intersection of the business, software development, data science, and user experience to create innovative products and intuitive user experiences to reduce the stress of traveling. You will have a competitive understanding of the travel landscape to facilitate the creation of successful new features. On any given day - whether youre weighing the tradeoffs of offering new features, scoping and specifying solutions with partners, or shepherding features through development - your contribution will be critical to Hoppers current and future success.\n\n\n\n\nLeveraging data science to solve customers problems is in Hoppers DNA. While this began with helping customers save money by booking at the best time with our Price Prediction, weve also built a suite of novel Fintech products which help customers save money, retain optionality to cancel or change their trips as needed, and help them seamlessly rebook when they run into problems during their travel.\n\n\n\n\nThis position is on the Disruption team, focused on solving that last problem. Hopper offers a product called Premium Disruption Assistance that helps our customers navigate flight delays, cancellations, or missed connections, and ultimately get where they want to be. If a customer experiences a disruption, they can rebook themselves on any airline  for free  or get a 100% refund of their trip cost. The Disruption team is expanding rapidly by creating new products, offering our existing products in new distribution channels, and scaling the business into an enterprise. As the Product Manager for the Disruption team, you are part of a cross functional team that is dedicated to this specific product; you will have immense impact, experience no gatekeeping, and no competing priorities, allowing you to truly focus on product work and your customers!\n\n\nWhat would your day-to-day look like:\nManage a product roadmap across several different business objectives, ensuring that we are executing against the highest impact items at any given time, and deliver things on time.\nWork closely with external partners on new and existing implementations; earn and maintain trust by building good relationships.\nRapidly test sound hypotheses through new merchandising experiments at different points in the customer journey to increase revenue\nTalk to customers frequently to gather qualitative data, and quantify it, to deeply understand their problems (and/or our opportunities); survey customers frequently to collect feedback\nConduct market research to understand traveler needs in different regions of the world\nUse data to identify user behavior and purchase patterns, which directly lead to hypotheses around opportunities that can be measurably validated/invalidated through simple experiments\nBuild new products, end to end: from idea to research to design to development to customer service to optimization. This person will launch things from the ground up and grow them into mature products.\nWork with customer service to understand and identify customer problem trends\nWork with back-end and front-end engineers, designers, legal, and many other stakeholders to launch innovative features quickly and bug-free\nLearn and use a diverse set of tools, especially analytics tools\n\n\nAn ideal candidate has:\nThrived in a consumer product role and delivered delightful features at scale\nStrong experience, knowledge of, and/or keen interest in Fintech, Insurtech, or risk-based products\nAn innovative and detail-oriented approach to problem-solving\nB2B and B2C experience\nAbility to navigate both the forest and the trees. Extreme attention to detail, and simultaneously the ability to think and operate strategically.\nExceptional ability to grasp, manage, and articulate complex systems\nExperience connecting innovative solutions to real-world, user problems with actual business needs of a rapidly scaling organization\nTechnical depth that allows you to communicate with, understand, and earn the respect of world-class engineers and data scientists\nA track record of being proactive and persuading colleagues by constructing a compelling narrative both in-person and in-writing\nPast success analyzing data, drawing accurate conclusions, and adjusting strategy accordingly\nNo ego, and a strong focus on doing what is right for the customer and the company\n\n\nPerks and benefits of working with us:\nWell-funded and proven startup with large ambitions, competitive salary and upsides of pre-IPO equity packages\nHopper covers 100% of the premiums for group insurance plan through Sun life Financial. You will have a competitive understanding of the travel landscape to facilitate the creation of successful new features. On any given day - whether youre weighing the tradeoffs of offering new features, scoping and specifying solutions with partners, or shepherding features through development - your contribution will be critical to Hoppers current and future success.\n\n\n\n\nLeveraging data science to solve customers problems is in Hoppers DNA. While this began with helping customers save money by booking at the best time with our Price Prediction, weve also built a suite of novel Fintech products which help customers save money, retain optionality to cancel or change their trips as needed, and help them seamlessly rebook when they run into problems during their travel.\n\n\n\n\nThis position is on the Disruption team, focused on solving that last problem. Hopper offers a product called Premium Disruption Assistance that helps our customers navigate flight delays, cancellations, or missed connections, and ultimately get where they want to be. If a customer experiences a disruption, they can rebook themselves on any airline  for free  or get a 100% refund of their trip cost. The Disruption team is expanding rapidly by creating new products, offering our existing products in new distribution channels, and scaling the business into an enterprise.
